title: Drow Racial quest
data:
The **[Drow](/wiki/Drow "Drow") Racial quest** sees you traveling from your family's fortress to kill [Seyll Auzkovyn](/wiki/Seyll_Auzkovyn "Seyll Auzkovyn") and retrieve her [Silver Starlight](/wiki/DNetHack_Artifacts#Silver_Starlight "DNetHack Artifacts"). When the character does confront Seyll, she will give her the option to switch sides and instead assassinate [Eclavdra](/wiki/Eclavdra "Eclavdra"), the original quest leader. For more information on the quest [branch](/wiki/Branch "Branch") in general, see the [quest](/wiki/Quest "Quest") article.

This quest is for female Drow [Priests](/wiki/Priest "Priest"), [Rangers](/wiki/Ranger "Ranger"), [Rogues](/wiki/Rogue "Rogue"), and [Wizards](/wiki/Wizard "Wizard"). Male Drow (Hedrow) of these roles get the [Hedrow shared quest](/index.php?title=Hedrow_shared_quest\&action=edit\&redlink=1 "Hedrow shared quest (page does not exist)") instead.

### Entry

First time:

```
You arrive in familiar surroundings.  In the distance, you <see|sense>
Erelhei-Cinlu, a great city of the Drow.

Your house's fortress is close before you. Something is wrong,
though.  The silver star of Lolth, token of the high council of
the matron mothers, is set over the gates.
```

Next time:

```
Once again, you stand outside Erelhei-Cinlu.
```

```
You have the oddest feeling that this may be the last time you

### Quest guardians

If #chatting before the quest is complete:

```
"You have been granted an audience with Eclavdra.  Don't keep her waiting!"
"The heretics of Eilistraee are besieging the city!"
"Eclavdra will see to those pale-elf loving freaks."
"The path to the surface passes through the drider caves. 
Those failed priestesses have little respect for their betters!"
"Hail Lolth!"
```

If #chatting after the quest is complete:

```
"You have been granted an audience with Eclavdra.  Don't keep her waiting!"
"The heretics of Eilistraee have been routed, praise be to Lolth!"
"Eclavdra certainly saw to those pale-elf loving freaks."
"I hope you taught those acursed (sic) driders some respect!"
"Hail Lolth!"
```

### Quest leader

When you first meet your quest leader:

```
"<playername>!  It is good that you have answered my summons.
Lolth requires your talents.

"But first, I must evaluate your abilities, to see if you 
have the required abilities to take on this holy mission."
```

When you return, having been rejected due to lack of experience:

```
"Once again, <playername>, you stand in our midst.  Are you ready now?"
```

This message is not currently used:

```
"Ah, you are here again, <playername>.  I will test your readiness..."
```

When you are expelled from the quest for having failed the alignment test seven times:

```
"<playername>!  You have doomed yourself.  You fairly radiate lawful influences,
showing your treachery for all to see.

"You are hereby banished!  I revoke the grace of Lolth from you!"
```

When being rejected due to lack of experience:

```
"<playername>, you are yet too inexperienced to withstand the demands of
Lolth's holy mission.  An An'kin might just be able to do this thing.

"Return to us when you are worthy of this honor."
```

When being rejected due to having worse than pious alignment:

```
"You have strayed, <playername>!  You know that Lolth requires
that we maintain a pure devotion to things chaotic!

"Return when you have purified yourself, and not before!"
```

When finally assigned the quest:

```
"You are indeed ready, <playername>.  This is your mission,
your holy quest from Lolth:

"The heretics of Eilistraee, treacherous daughter of Lolth,
have been sending missionaries into the city, infecting
our citizens with their debased teachings.

"This outrage cannot be alowed to stand. Your mission is
to travel through the drider caves and up to the surface,
locate the grove of Eilistraee, and kill her heretic
priestess.  Bring me Silver Starlight, her unholy sword,
as proof of your deed!

"Do this, and know the glory of Lolth! Fail, and know
everlasting torment! Go now!"
```

```
"There are many secret passages in the drider caves."
"Why are you still here?  Get on with it, or face the wrath of Lolth!"
"Go now!"
"Serve Lolth in all things!"
"The Eilistraee heretics seek to bring down the clergy of Lolth."
"Eilistraee and her followers have always hated us."
"The blasphemous missionaries have set off a quake that shall bury
them alive!"
"Driders are strong, but they enjoy not the favor of Lolth."
"You tempt the wrath of Lolth with your delay."
"The heretics have formed a blasphemous alliance with the surface
elves."
```

```
You descend into the outer regions of the drider caves.  You can hear
scuffling sounds in the corridors, and vague mumblings in the distance.

You know that there were many secret passageways in this complex.
```

When returning:

```
Once again, you descend into the drider caves.
```

When first entering the goal level:

```
You have arrived at the Grove of Eilistraee.  The accursed sunlight still
fills your eyes with painful darkness, but in the center of the trees 
you can hear voices raised in song, singing naive, heathen melodies in
honor of the bitch-goddess Eilistraee.
```

When returning:

```
Once again, you enter the Grove of Eilistraee.
```

### Quest nemesis

When first encountering the quest nemesis:

```
"Wait, <playername>!?  <playername>, is it really you?  It's me, Seyll Auzkovyn!

"We were friends as girls, do you not recall?  Has Eclavdra sent you to 
kill me?  She is using you, decieving you. She fears to come and 
confront me herself, fears to leave the Underdark and face the sunlight.

"Please, give me a chance!  What we were taught as girls is not the truth.
Lolth is a wicked deity, not worthy of our service.  She has turned 
generations of drow against one another for her own amusement, just as she
has turned us against each other now.  Think, what the drow could do,
if we did not kill nine-tenths of our daughters in futile fratricide and
assassinations!

"We have a chance to break this cycle!  If we can free Erelhei-Cinlu from
the clergy of Lolth, our acts will reverberate from one side of the 
Underdark to the other!"
```

Upon further meetings:

```
"Please, speak to me!"
```

And on the 4th and subsequent meetings:

```
"Lolth is not worthy of your service!"
```

When you have Silver Starlight, but Seyll Auzkovyn is still alive:

```
"That blade was a gift from Eilistraee!"
```

#### Discouragement

Seyll Auzkovyn will occasionally utter "maledictions":

```
"Lolth has turned us against each other!"
"Think of your daughters! Do you want their blood spilt in petty squabbles!?"
"Help us end this!"
"Please don't make me kill you!"
"We have a chance to break this cycle!"
"Eclavdra is using you!"
"Help me free Erelhei-Cinlu!"
"What we were taught as girls is not the truth!"
"Don't you remember your sister!?  Did you truly feel nothing, when you
drove the blade into her heart!?  Help me put an end to the killing!"
"You must not stop me.  I'll kill you, if I must!  But please, trust 
me!  Talk to me instead!"
```

### Victory

When picking up your quest artifact:

```
The wind plays a mornful tune as it blows over Silver Starlight, 
but it stops when you pick it up.  Eclavdra will accept this blade
as proof that you have truly killed Seyll Auzkovyn.
```

When killing the nemesis:

```
Seyll Auzkovyn falls to her knees, her life's-blood running down her chest and
onto the grass.

    Perhaps- *cough* Perhaps I was a fool to think I could change
    the drow.  Perhaps I was a fool to stand against Lolth.
    
    But please, <playername>, don't forget me!  Remember what I told you,
    and you may yet escape the knife!

She shivers for a moment longer, then lies still.
```

When returning to your quest leader:

```
"<playername>!  You have destroyed the foul heretics!  I only wish Seyll Auzkovyn 
had been taken alive, I would have liked to ... instruct her as to 
the error of her ways.

"Your name will be entered in the annals of Lolth, and the tale of how
we bested the hordes of the traitor goddess Eilistraee will be told for
generations to come.

"You must now return to the Dungeons of Doom and your quest for the 
Amulet of Yendor.  With that divine relic, Lolth will finally be able
to put down her rebellious daughter!

"Take Silver Starlight with you, if you wish.  Otherwise, you can take the 
Wrathful Spider, with which to kill your foes from a distance."
```

When subsequently throwing Silver Starlight to Eclavdra:

```
"This weapon was made by the surface elves for the high priestess
of Eilistraee, Seyll Auzkovyn.  Befitting their obsession with frivolous music,
it has a flute built into the handle.  It can also be used to create
throwing stars, and imparts a silvery sheen to such weapons.

"Would you like to use this weapon in your quest, or would you 
prefer the ancient droven crossbow, the Wrathful Spider?"
```

When subsequently throwing the Wrathful Spider to Eclavdra:

```
"This crossbow was made in the earliest days of our empire in
the Underdark.  With it, one need never run out of bolts.  
Unlike lesser crossbows, it can also fire multiple bolts in
one volley, though the damage inflicted by each bolt is not
so great."
```

### Post-quest

When talking to Eclavdra after the quest:

```
"How have you fared on your holy quest for the Amulet
of Yendor?  Lolth does not tolerate failure!"
```

When talking to Eclavdra after getting the [Amulet](/wiki/Amulet_of_Yendor "Amulet of Yendor"):

```
"You have it!  You have recovered the Amulet of Yendor!

"Whoever brings that to Lolth's high altar in the astral plane will
be exhalted above all others, and shall even be granted the rank of
demigoddess!

"I have been searching for that Amulet for many long years.  To 
think a mere <currentrank> would find it first!

"Well, I thank you for bringing it to me.  Your part in this
is done.

"Now DIE!"
```

Eye, the chained god Tharizdun, who seeks to consume all the
worlds and all the gods thereof.

Eclavdra and Zuggtmoy both betrayed the Eye, and each other, having 
planned from the beginning to use it for their own ends.  Any 
interaction with the Chained One is perilous, however, and its
service is not easy to foreswear.  It was likely Tharizdun who
sent the black tentacles that claimed Eclavdra as she lay dying.

"The Rod itself seems free of the taint of its father, however,
and there is little doubt that it is a powerful tool, 
capable of augmenting spellcasting and multiple debilitating 
attacks in melee.

"Would you like to use this weapon in your quest, or would you
prefer the Crescent Blade of Eilistraee?"
```

When subsequently throwing the Crescent Blade to Seyll Auzkovyn:

```
"This blade was forged by Eilistraee as a weapon against her
mother, Lolth.  It's pale moon-fires pass through armor, and
it can cleave even the head of a goddess from her shoulders."
```

### Post-quest

When talking to Seyll Auzkovyn after the quest:

```
"Welcome back, <playername>.  How have you fared on your quest for the
Amulet of Yendor?"
```

When talking to Seyll Auzkovyn after getting the [Amulet](/wiki/Amulet_of_Yendor "Amulet of Yendor"):

```
"You have it!  You have recovered the Amulet of Yendor!
Now, I will tell you what must be done:

"The Amulet has within it magic, the capability to transport you to
the Astral Plane, where the high altar of Eilistraee resides.

"To activate this magic, you must travel upwards as far as you can.
When you reach the temple, sacrifice the Amulet to Eilistraee.

"Thus will you fulfill your destiny."
```

Drow Racial quest

From NetHackWiki
Jump to navigation Jump to search

The Drow Racial quest sees you traveling from your family's fortress to kill Seyll Auzkovyn and retrieve her Silver Starlight. When the character does confront Seyll, she will give her the option to switch sides and instead assassinate Eclavdra, the original quest leader. For more information on the quest branch in general, see the quest article.

This quest is for female Drow Priests, Rangers, Rogues, and Wizards. Male Drow (Hedrow) of these roles get the Hedrow shared quest instead.

Messages

Entry

First time: 

You arrive in familiar surroundings.  In the distance, you <see|sense>
Erelhei-Cinlu, a great city of the Drow.

Your house's fortress is close before you. Something is wrong,
though.  The silver star of Lolth, token of the high council of
the matron mothers, is set over the gates.

Next time: 

Once again, you stand outside Erelhei-Cinlu.

If already rejected twice due to bad alignment: 

You have the oddest feeling that this may be the last time you
are to vist (sic) Erelhei-Cinlu.

Quest guardians

If #chatting before the quest is complete: 

"You have been granted an audience with Eclavdra.  Don't keep her waiting!"
"The heretics of Eilistraee are besieging the city!"
"Eclavdra will see to those pale-elf loving freaks."
"The path to the surface passes through the drider caves. 
Those failed priestesses have little respect for their betters!"
"Hail Lolth!"

If #chatting after the quest is complete: 

"You have been granted an audience with Eclavdra.  Don't keep her waiting!"
"The heretics of Eilistraee have been routed, praise be to Lolth!"
"Eclavdra certainly saw to those pale-elf loving freaks."
"I hope you taught those acursed (sic) driders some respect!"
"Hail Lolth!"

Quest leader

When you first meet your quest leader: 

"<playername>!  It is good that you have answered my summons.
Lolth requires your talents.

"But first, I must evaluate your abilities, to see if you 
have the required abilities to take on this holy mission."

When you return, having been rejected due to lack of experience: 

"Once again, <playername>, you stand in our midst.  Are you ready now?"

This message is not currently used: 

"Ah, you are here again, <playername>.  I will test your readiness..."

When you are expelled from the quest for having failed the alignment test seven times: 

"<playername>!  You have doomed yourself.  You fairly radiate lawful influences,
showing your treachery for all to see.

"You are hereby banished!  I revoke the grace of Lolth from you!"

When being rejected due to lack of experience: 

"<playername>, you are yet too inexperienced to withstand the demands of
Lolth's holy mission.  An An'kin might just be able to do this thing.

"Return to us when you are worthy of this honor."

When being rejected due to having worse than pious alignment: 

"You have strayed, <playername>!  You know that Lolth requires
that we maintain a pure devotion to things chaotic!

"Return when you have purified yourself, and not before!"

When finally assigned the quest: 

"You are indeed ready, <playername>.  This is your mission,
your holy quest from Lolth:

"The heretics of Eilistraee, treacherous daughter of Lolth,
have been sending missionaries into the city, infecting
our citizens with their debased teachings.

"This outrage cannot be alowed to stand. Your mission is
to travel through the drider caves and up to the surface,
locate the grove of Eilistraee, and kill her heretic
priestess.  Bring me Silver Starlight, her unholy sword,
as proof of your deed!

"Do this, and know the glory of Lolth! Fail, and know
everlasting torment! Go now!"

Encouragement

If you subsequently chat to your quest leader, you are encouraged: 

"There are many secret passages in the drider caves."
"Why are you still here?  Get on with it, or face the wrath of Lolth!"
"Go now!"
"Serve Lolth in all things!"
"The Eilistraee heretics seek to bring down the clergy of Lolth."
"Eilistraee and her followers have always hated us."
"The blasphemous missionaries have set off a quake that shall bury
them alive!"
"Driders are strong, but they enjoy not the favor of Lolth."
"You tempt the wrath of Lolth with your delay."
"The heretics have formed a blasphemous alliance with the surface
elves."

Locate and goal levels

When first entering the locate level: 

You descend into the outer regions of the drider caves.  You can hear
scuffling sounds in the corridors, and vague mumblings in the distance.

You know that there were many secret passageways in this complex.

When returning: 

Once again, you descend into the drider caves.

When first entering the goal level: 

You have arrived at the Grove of Eilistraee.  The accursed sunlight still
fills your eyes with painful darkness, but in the center of the trees 
you can hear voices raised in song, singing naive, heathen melodies in
honor of the bitch-goddess Eilistraee.

When returning: 

Once again, you enter the Grove of Eilistraee.

Quest nemesis

When first encountering the quest nemesis: 

"Wait, <playername>!?  <playername>, is it really you?  It's me, Seyll Auzkovyn!

"We were friends as girls, do you not recall?  Has Eclavdra sent you to 
kill me?  She is using you, decieving you. She fears to come and 
confront me herself, fears to leave the Underdark and face the sunlight.

"Please, give me a chance!  What we were taught as girls is not the truth.
Lolth is a wicked deity, not worthy of our service.  She has turned 
generations of drow against one another for her own amusement, just as she
has turned us against each other now.  Think, what the drow could do,
if we did not kill nine-tenths of our daughters in futile fratricide and
assassinations!

"We have a chance to break this cycle!  If we can free Erelhei-Cinlu from
the clergy of Lolth, our acts will reverberate from one side of the 
Underdark to the other!"

Upon further meetings: 

"Please, speak to me!"

And on the 4th and subsequent meetings: 

"Lolth is not worthy of your service!"

When you have Silver Starlight, but Seyll Auzkovyn is still alive: 

"That blade was a gift from Eilistraee!"

Discouragement

Seyll Auzkovyn will occasionally utter "maledictions": 

"Lolth has turned us against each other!"
"Think of your daughters! Do you want their blood spilt in petty squabbles!?"
"Help us end this!"
"Please don't make me kill you!"
"We have a chance to break this cycle!"
"Eclavdra is using you!"
"Help me free Erelhei-Cinlu!"
"What we were taught as girls is not the truth!"
"Don't you remember your sister!?  Did you truly feel nothing, when you
drove the blade into her heart!?  Help me put an end to the killing!"
"You must not stop me.  I'll kill you, if I must!  But please, trust 
me!  Talk to me instead!"

Victory

When picking up your quest artifact: 

The wind plays a mornful tune as it blows over Silver Starlight, 
but it stops when you pick it up.  Eclavdra will accept this blade
as proof that you have truly killed Seyll Auzkovyn.

When killing the nemesis: 

Seyll Auzkovyn falls to her knees, her life's-blood running down her chest and
onto the grass.

    Perhaps- *cough* Perhaps I was a fool to think I could change
    the drow.  Perhaps I was a fool to stand against Lolth.
    
    But please, <playername>, don't forget me!  Remember what I told you,
    and you may yet escape the knife!

She shivers for a moment longer, then lies still.

When returning to your quest leader: 

"<playername>!  You have destroyed the foul heretics!  I only wish Seyll Auzkovyn 
had been taken alive, I would have liked to ... instruct her as to 
the error of her ways.

"Your name will be entered in the annals of Lolth, and the tale of how
we bested the hordes of the traitor goddess Eilistraee will be told for
generations to come.

"You must now return to the Dungeons of Doom and your quest for the 
Amulet of Yendor.  With that divine relic, Lolth will finally be able
to put down her rebellious daughter!

"Take Silver Starlight with you, if you wish.  Otherwise, you can take the 
Wrathful Spider, with which to kill your foes from a distance."

When subsequently throwing Silver Starlight to Eclavdra: 

"This weapon was made by the surface elves for the high priestess
of Eilistraee, Seyll Auzkovyn.  Befitting their obsession with frivolous music,
it has a flute built into the handle.  It can also be used to create
throwing stars, and imparts a silvery sheen to such weapons.

"Would you like to use this weapon in your quest, or would you 
prefer the ancient droven crossbow, the Wrathful Spider?"

When subsequently throwing the Wrathful Spider to Eclavdra: 

"This crossbow was made in the earliest days of our empire in
the Underdark.  With it, one need never run out of bolts.  
Unlike lesser crossbows, it can also fire multiple bolts in
one volley, though the damage inflicted by each bolt is not
so great."

Post-quest

When talking to Eclavdra after the quest: 

"How have you fared on your holy quest for the Amulet
of Yendor?  Lolth does not tolerate failure!"

When talking to Eclavdra after getting the Amulet: 

"You have it!  You have recovered the Amulet of Yendor!

"Whoever brings that to Lolth's high altar in the astral plane will
be exhalted above all others, and shall even be granted the rank of
demigoddess!

"I have been searching for that Amulet for many long years.  To 
think a mere <currentrank> would find it first!

"Well, I thank you for bringing it to me.  Your part in this
is done.

"Now DIE!"

Messages if you switch sides

Entry

The first time you return to the Grove of Eilistraee after switching sides: 

You have returned to the Grove of Eilistraee, home base of the 
rebellion against the clergy of Lolth.

Subsequent visits: 

Once again, you have returned to the Grove of Eilistraee, 
home base of the rebellion against the clergy of Lolth.

Quest guardians

If #chatting before the quest is complete: 

"We are so glad that you were able to shake off the webs of Lolth!"
"The followers of Lolth have launched several assaults on this Grove!"
"Seyll Auzkovyn was so relieved that you sided with us."
"You will have to go back through the Drider caves to reach
Erelhei-Cinlu. Though Lolth has betrayed them, the driders 
have little use for the followers of Eilistraee!"
"Eilistraee is not like her mother.  She saved us from the dark."

If #chatting after the quest is complete: 

"We are so very glad that you were able to shake off the webs of Lolth!"
"The followers of Lolth have been thrown into disarray!"
"It's been a long time since I've seen Seyll Auzkovyn so happy."
"I hope you didn't have to kill many of those unfortunate driders."
"You have saved us and our goddess from the dark."

Quest leader

When you are given the quest: 

"<playername>!  I am so glad that you decided to trust us!

"I think you already know what I must ask you to do:"

"We had initially hoped to avoid bloodshed altogether,
sending missionaries into Erelhei-Cinlu to start an underground
religious countermovement.  And, indeed, met with some 
initial success.  However, our efforts enraged Lolth, and
Eclavdra, high priestess of Lolth, led a bloody purge of 
our missionaries and converts.

"Eclavdra has since taken the offensive against us,
orchestrating a wide variety of assassination attempts
and outright assaults.  I now see that we must carry the
fight to Eclavdra and the matron-mothers if we are to have
any chance of freeing Erelhei-Cinlu from Lolth's webs.

"You must be our sword in this.  You will be able to 
pass through the perimeter of Erelhei-Cinlu unchallenged.
With a little good fortune, no one will know you've 
joined Eilistraee before you confront Eclavdra!

When you are expelled from the quest for having changed alignment: 

"<playername>!  I thought I could trust you!  In your treachery, you have
doomed yourself.  Lolth has revoked her grace from you, and now
you have turned your back on Eilistraee as well.  I banish you
to The Dungeons of Doom, and I pray to all the gods you one day find peace!

Encouragement

If you subsequently chat to your quest leader, you are encouraged: 

"There are many secret passages in the drider caves."
"Good luck!"
"Eilistraee will be with you, I know it."
"Lolth and her clergy must fall!"
"We must free the drow!"
"Go swiftly and silently."
"For the sake of all drow, we must not fail!"
"Watch out for driders."
"Beware the wrath of Lolth.  Eclavdra will not be an easy opponent."
"Eclavdra made a critical error, coming to the outskirts of Erelhei-Cinlu."

Locate and goal levels

When first entering the locate level: 

You descend into the outer regions of the drider caves.  You can hear
scuffling sounds in the corridors, and vague mumblings in the distance.

You know that there were many secret passageways in this complex.

When returning: 

Once again, you descend into the drider caves.

When first entering the goal level: 

You have returned to you house's fortress on the outskirts of
Erelhei-Cinlu.  The silver star of Lolth is still set over the gates, token of
Eclavdra and the high council of the matron-mothers.

The hour of reckoning is at hand.

When returning: 

Once again, you have returned to Erelhei-Cinlu.

Quest nemesis

When first encountering the quest nemesis: 

"<playername>!  Lolth has told us of your treachery!  Prepare to die!

Upon further meetings: 

"Now you die!"

And on the 4th and subsequent meetings: 

"Accept your fate!  Die now!"

When you have the Tentacle Rod, but Eclavdra is still alive: 

"Give that back!"

Discouragement

Eclavdra will occasionally utter maledictions: 

"You dare turn against Lolth!?  Even in death you shall not know peace!"
""Seyll Auzkovyn is using you.  You won't survive this fight!"
"Even a drider's fate is too good for you!"
"I'll flay your soul!"
"Even a zombie's fate is too good for you!"
"You will never know peace!"
"I'll kill you and anyone who ever gave you shelter!"
"Your fate will be wispered (sic) of for generations to come!"
"You, a hero?  Don't make me laugh!  You killed two of your sisters,
stabbed one in the back and shot the other in the head, from ambush 
no less!  It was masterfully done!  What makes you think that 
Eilistraee would accept one such as you!"
"Your hands are as bloody as any of us!  Eilistraee or Lolth, you
will burn!"

Victory

When picking up your quest artifact: 

The Rod's tentacles wave languidly at you as you pick it up.  There
is something unwholesome about this weapon.  You almost fear to let
it sense you.

When killing the nemesis: 

Eclavdra falls to her knees, blood running down her forehead and into
her eyes.  She curses you:

    You haven't seen the last of me.  You shall never escape
    the webs of Lolth...  and there are others still who would
    avenge me, who are bound to my aid by pacts sealed in blood!
    Gods of rot and decay and lust.  Enjoy your brief victory,
    I will have my re-

Her eyes go wide, and she vomits black ichor onto the ground.
Tentacles sprout from the stain, and from the corruption spreading
from her shadow.  The tentacles wave languidly for a moment, then
strike with frightening speed, dragging her down into the suddenly
contracting patch of corruption.

When returning to your quest leader: 

"<playername>!  You did it!  We'll use the opening you have given us to send
the missionaries back in.  With a little help from Eilistraee, 
we'll free this whole city from Lolth's foul webs!

"If you're willing, you should now return to the Dungeons of Doom 
and your quest for the Amulet of Yendor.  With that divine relic, 
Eilistraee will finally be able to battle Lolth on equal footing,
or even from a position of greater power!"

"Take the Tentacle Rod with you, if you wish.  Otherwise, Eilistraee will gift
you her greatest instrument, the Crescent Blade, that can cleave
even the necks of goddesses!"

When subsequently throwing the Tentacle Rod to Seyll Auzkovyn: 

"This rod was gifted to Eclavdra while she served Zuggtmoy, demon
lady of rot and corruption, then consort of the Elder Elemental
Eye, the chained god Tharizdun, who seeks to consume all the
worlds and all the gods thereof.

Eclavdra and Zuggtmoy both betrayed the Eye, and each other, having 
planned from the beginning to use it for their own ends.  Any 
interaction with the Chained One is perilous, however, and its
service is not easy to foreswear.  It was likely Tharizdun who
sent the black tentacles that claimed Eclavdra as she lay dying.

"The Rod itself seems free of the taint of its father, however,
and there is little doubt that it is a powerful tool, 
capable of augmenting spellcasting and multiple debilitating 
attacks in melee.

"Would you like to use this weapon in your quest, or would you
prefer the Crescent Blade of Eilistraee?"

When subsequently throwing the Crescent Blade to Seyll Auzkovyn: 

"This blade was forged by Eilistraee as a weapon against her
mother, Lolth.  It's pale moon-fires pass through armor, and
it can cleave even the head of a goddess from her shoulders."

Post-quest

When talking to Seyll Auzkovyn after the quest: 

"Welcome back, <playername>.  How have you fared on your quest for the
Amulet of Yendor?"

When talking to Seyll Auzkovyn after getting the Amulet: 

"You have it!  You have recovered the Amulet of Yendor!
Now, I will tell you what must be done:

"The Amulet has within it magic, the capability to transport you to
the Astral Plane, where the high altar of Eilistraee resides.

"To activate this magic, you must travel upwards as far as you can.
When you reach the temple, sacrifice the Amulet to Eilistraee.

"Thus will you fulfill your destiny."

The '''[[Drow]] Racial quest''' sees you traveling from your family's fortress to kill [[Seyll Auzkovyn]] and retrieve her [[DNetHack_Artifacts#Silver_Starlight|Silver Starlight]]. When the character does confront Seyll, she will give her the option to switch sides and instead assassinate [[Eclavdra]], the original quest leader. For more information on the quest [[branch]] in general, see the [[quest]] article. This quest is for female Drow [[Priest]]s, [[Ranger]]s, [[Rogue]]s, and [[Wizard]]s. Male Drow (Hedrow) of these roles get the [[Hedrow shared quest]] instead. ==Maps== ===Home level===

The upstairs appear somewhere outside the central area where Seyll waits. Note that Seyll will offer to let the player switch sides, in which case she becomes the new quest leader, Eclavdra becomes the quest nemesis, and the [[DNetHack_Artifacts#Tentacle_Rod|Tentacle Rod]] becomes the quest artifact. ==Messages== ===Entry=== First time: You arrive in familiar surroundings. In the distance, you Erelhei-Cinlu, a great city of the Drow. Your house's fortress is close before you. Something is wrong, though. The silver star of Lolth, token of the high council of the matron mothers, is set over the gates. Next time: Once again, you stand outside Erelhei-Cinlu. If already rejected twice due to bad alignment: You have the oddest feeling that this may be the last time you are to vist (sic) Erelhei-Cinlu. ===Quest guardians=== If #chatting before the quest is complete: "You have been granted an audience with Eclavdra. Don't keep her waiting!" "The heretics of Eilistraee are besieging the city!" "Eclavdra will see to those pale-elf loving freaks." "The path to the surface passes through the drider caves. Those failed priestesses have little respect for their betters!" "Hail Lolth!" If #chatting after the quest is complete: "You have been granted an audience with Eclavdra. Don't keep her waiting!" "The heretics of Eilistraee have been routed, praise be to Lolth!" "Eclavdra certainly saw to those pale-elf loving freaks." "I hope you taught those acursed (sic) driders some respect!" "Hail Lolth!" ===Quest leader=== When you first meet your quest leader: "! It is good that you have answered my summons. Lolth requires your talents. "But first, I must evaluate your abilities, to see if you have the required abilities to take on this holy mission." When you return, having been rejected due to lack of experience: "Once again, , you stand in our midst. Are you ready now?" This message is not currently used: "Ah, you are here again, . I will test your readiness..." When you are expelled from the quest for having failed the alignment test seven times: "! You have doomed yourself. You fairly radiate lawful influences, showing your treachery for all to see. "You are hereby banished! I revoke the grace of Lolth from you!" When being rejected due to lack of experience: ", you are yet too inexperienced to withstand the demands of Lolth's holy mission. An An'kin might just be able to do this thing. "Return to us when you are worthy of this honor." When being rejected due to having worse than pious alignment: "You have strayed, ! You know that Lolth requires that we maintain a pure devotion to things chaotic! "Return when you have purified yourself, and not before!" When finally assigned the quest: "You are indeed ready, . This is your mission, your holy quest from Lolth: "The heretics of Eilistraee, treacherous daughter of Lolth, have been sending missionaries into the city, infecting our citizens with their debased teachings. "This outrage cannot be alowed to stand. Your mission is to travel through the drider caves and up to the surface, locate the grove of Eilistraee, and kill her heretic priestess. Bring me Silver Starlight, her unholy sword, as proof of your deed! "Do this, and know the glory of Lolth! Fail, and know everlasting torment! Go now!" ====Encouragement==== If you subsequently chat to your quest leader, you are encouraged: "There are many secret passages in the drider caves." "Why are you still here? Get on with it, or face the wrath of Lolth!" "Go now!" "Serve Lolth in all things!" "The Eilistraee heretics seek to bring down the clergy of Lolth." "Eilistraee and her followers have always hated us." "The blasphemous missionaries have set off a quake that shall bury them alive!" "Driders are strong, but they enjoy not the favor of Lolth." "You tempt the wrath of Lolth with your delay." "The heretics have formed a blasphemous alliance with the surface elves." ===Locate and goal levels=== When first entering the locate level: You descend into the outer regions of the drider caves. You can hear scuffling sounds in the corridors, and vague mumblings in the distance. You know that there were many secret passageways in this complex. When returning: Once again, you descend into the drider caves. When first entering the goal level: You have arrived at the Grove of Eilistraee. The accursed sunlight still fills your eyes with painful darkness, but in the center of the trees you can hear voices raised in song, singing naive, heathen melodies in honor of the bitch-goddess Eilistraee. When returning: Once again, you enter the Grove of Eilistraee. ===Quest nemesis=== When first encountering the quest nemesis: "Wait, !? , is it really you? It's me, Seyll Auzkovyn! "We were friends as girls, do you not recall? Has Eclavdra sent you to kill me? She is using you, decieving you. She fears to come and confront me herself, fears to leave the Underdark and face the sunlight. "Please, give me a chance! What we were taught as girls is not the truth. Lolth is a wicked deity, not worthy of our service. She has turned generations of drow against one another for her own amusement, just as she has turned us against each other now. Think, what the drow could do, if we did not kill nine-tenths of our daughters in futile fratricide and assassinations! "We have a chance to break this cycle! If we can free Erelhei-Cinlu from the clergy of Lolth, our acts will reverberate from one side of the Underdark to the other!" Upon further meetings: "Please, speak to me!" And on the 4th and subsequent meetings: "Lolth is not worthy of your service!" When you have Silver Starlight, but Seyll Auzkovyn is still alive: "That blade was a gift from Eilistraee!" ====Discouragement==== Seyll Auzkovyn will occasionally utter "maledictions": "Lolth has turned us against each other!" "Think of your daughters! Do you want their blood spilt in petty squabbles!?" "Help us end this!" "Please don't make me kill you!" "We have a chance to break this cycle!" "Eclavdra is using you!" "Help me free Erelhei-Cinlu!" "What we were taught as girls is not the truth!" "Don't you remember your sister!? Did you truly feel nothing, when you drove the blade into her heart!? Help me put an end to the killing!" "You must not stop me. I'll kill you, if I must! But please, trust me! Talk to me instead!" ===Victory=== When picking up your quest artifact: The wind plays a mornful tune as it blows over Silver Starlight, but it stops when you pick it up. Eclavdra will accept this blade as proof that you have truly killed Seyll Auzkovyn. When killing the nemesis: Seyll Auzkovyn falls to her knees, her life's-blood running down her chest and onto the grass. Perhaps- *cough* Perhaps I was a fool to think I could change the drow. Perhaps I was a fool to stand against Lolth. But please, , don't forget me! Remember what I told you, and you may yet escape the knife! She shivers for a moment longer, then lies still. When returning to your quest leader: "! You have destroyed the foul heretics! I only wish Seyll Auzkovyn had been taken alive, I would have liked to ... instruct her as to the error of her ways. "Your name will be entered in the annals of Lolth, and the tale of how we bested the hordes of the traitor goddess Eilistraee will be told for generations to come. "You must now return to the Dungeons of Doom and your quest for the Amulet of Yendor. With that divine relic, Lolth will finally be able to put down her rebellious daughter! "Take Silver Starlight with you, if you wish. Otherwise, you can take the Wrathful Spider, with which to kill your foes from a distance." When subsequently throwing Silver Starlight to Eclavdra: "This weapon was made by the surface elves for the high priestess of Eilistraee, Seyll Auzkovyn. Befitting their obsession with frivolous music, it has a flute built into the handle. It can also be used to create throwing stars, and imparts a silvery sheen to such weapons. "Would you like to use this weapon in your quest, or would you prefer the ancient droven crossbow, the Wrathful Spider?" When subsequently throwing the Wrathful Spider to Eclavdra: "This crossbow was made in the earliest days of our empire in the Underdark. With it, one need never run out of bolts. Unlike lesser crossbows, it can also fire multiple bolts in one volley, though the damage inflicted by each bolt is not so great." ===Post-quest=== When talking to Eclavdra after the quest: "How have you fared on your holy quest for the Amulet of Yendor? Lolth does not tolerate failure!" When talking to Eclavdra after getting the [[Amulet of Yendor|Amulet]]: "You have it! You have recovered the Amulet of Yendor! "Whoever brings that to Lolth's high altar in the astral plane will be exhalted above all others, and shall even be granted the rank of demigoddess! "I have been searching for that Amulet for many long years. To think a mere would find it first! "Well, I thank you for bringing it to me. Your part in this is done. "Now DIE!" ==Messages if you switch sides== ===Entry=== The first time you return to the Grove of Eilistraee after switching sides: You have returned to the Grove of Eilistraee, home base of the rebellion against the clergy of Lolth. Subsequent visits: Once again, you have returned to the Grove of Eilistraee, home base of the rebellion against the clergy of Lolth. ===Quest guardians=== If #chatting before the quest is complete: "We are so glad that you were able to shake off the webs of Lolth!" "The followers of Lolth have launched several assaults on this Grove!" "Seyll Auzkovyn was so relieved that you sided with us." "You will have to go back through the Drider caves to reach Erelhei-Cinlu. Though Lolth has betrayed them, the driders have little use for the followers of Eilistraee!" "Eilistraee is not like her mother. She saved us from the dark." If #chatting after the quest is complete: "We are so very glad that you were able to shake off the webs of Lolth!" "The followers of Lolth have been thrown into disarray!" "It's been a long time since I've seen Seyll Auzkovyn so happy." "I hope you didn't have to kill many of those unfortunate driders." "You have saved us and our goddess from the dark." ===Quest leader=== When you are given the quest: "! I am so glad that you decided to trust us! "I think you already know what I must ask you to do:" "We had initially hoped to avoid bloodshed altogether, sending missionaries into Erelhei-Cinlu to start an underground religious countermovement. And, indeed, met with some initial success. However, our efforts enraged Lolth, and Eclavdra, high priestess of Lolth, led a bloody purge of our missionaries and converts. "Eclavdra has since taken the offensive against us, orchestrating a wide variety of assassination attempts and outright assaults. I now see that we must carry the fight to Eclavdra and the matron-mothers if we are to have any chance of freeing Erelhei-Cinlu from Lolth's webs. "You must be our sword in this. You will be able to pass through the perimeter of Erelhei-Cinlu unchallenged. With a little good fortune, no one will know you've joined Eilistraee before you confront Eclavdra! When you are expelled from the quest for having changed alignment: "! I thought I could trust you! In your treachery, you have doomed yourself. Lolth has revoked her grace from you, and now you have turned your back on Eilistraee as well. I banish you to The Dungeons of Doom, and I pray to all the gods you one day find peace! ====Encouragement==== If you subsequently chat to your quest leader, you are encouraged: "There are many secret passages in the drider caves." "Good luck!" "Eilistraee will be with you, I know it." "Lolth and her clergy must fall!" "We must free the drow!" "Go swiftly and silently." "For the sake of all drow, we must not fail!" "Watch out for driders." "Beware the wrath of Lolth. Eclavdra will not be an easy opponent." "Eclavdra made a critical error, coming to the outskirts of Erelhei-Cinlu." ===Locate and goal levels=== When first entering the locate level: You descend into the outer regions of the drider caves. You can hear scuffling sounds in the corridors, and vague mumblings in the distance. You know that there were many secret passageways in this complex. When returning: Once again, you descend into the drider caves. When first entering the goal level: You have returned to you house's fortress on the outskirts of Erelhei-Cinlu. The silver star of Lolth is still set over the gates, token of Eclavdra and the high council of the matron-mothers. The hour of reckoning is at hand. When returning: Once again, you have returned to Erelhei-Cinlu. ===Quest nemesis=== When first encountering the quest nemesis: "! Lolth has told us of your treachery! Prepare to die! Upon further meetings: "Now you die!" And on the 4th and subsequent meetings: "Accept your fate! Die now!" When you have the Tentacle Rod, but Eclavdra is still alive: "Give that back!" ====Discouragement==== Eclavdra will occasionally utter maledictions: "You dare turn against Lolth!? Even in death you shall not know peace!" ""Seyll Auzkovyn is using you. You won't survive this fight!" "Even a drider's fate is too good for you!" "I'll flay your soul!" "Even a zombie's fate is too good for you!" "You will never know peace!" "I'll kill you and anyone who ever gave you shelter!" "Your fate will be wispered (sic) of for generations to come!" "You, a hero? Don't make me laugh! You killed two of your sisters, stabbed one in the back and shot the other in the head, from ambush no less! It was masterfully done! What makes you think that Eilistraee would accept one such as you!" "Your hands are as bloody as any of us! Eilistraee or Lolth, you will burn!" ===Victory=== When picking up your quest artifact: The Rod's tentacles wave languidly at you as you pick it up. There is something unwholesome about this weapon. You almost fear to let it sense you. When killing the nemesis: Eclavdra falls to her knees, blood running down her forehead and into her eyes. She curses you: You haven't seen the last of me. You shall never escape the webs of Lolth... and there are others still who would avenge me, who are bound to my aid by pacts sealed in blood! Gods of rot and decay and lust. Enjoy your brief victory, I will have my re- Her eyes go wide, and she vomits black ichor onto the ground. Tentacles sprout from the stain, and from the corruption spreading from her shadow. The tentacles wave languidly for a moment, then strike with frightening speed, dragging her down into the suddenly contracting patch of corruption. When returning to your quest leader: "! You did it! We'll use the opening you have given us to send the missionaries back in. With a little help from Eilistraee, we'll free this whole city from Lolth's foul webs! "If you're willing, you should now return to the Dungeons of Doom and your quest for the Amulet of Yendor. With that divine relic, Eilistraee will finally be able to battle Lolth on equal footing, or even from a position of greater power!" "Take the Tentacle Rod with you, if you wish. Otherwise, Eilistraee will gift you her greatest instrument, the Crescent Blade, that can cleave even the necks of goddesses!" When subsequently throwing the Tentacle Rod to Seyll Auzkovyn: "This rod was gifted to Eclavdra while she served Zuggtmoy, demon lady of rot and corruption, then consort of the Elder Elemental Eye, the chained god Tharizdun, who seeks to consume all the worlds and all the gods thereof. Eclavdra and Zuggtmoy both betrayed the Eye, and each other, having planned from the beginning to use it for their own ends. Any interaction with the Chained One is perilous, however, and its service is not easy to foreswear. It was likely Tharizdun who sent the black tentacles that claimed Eclavdra as she lay dying. "The Rod itself seems free of the taint of its father, however, and there is little doubt that it is a powerful tool, capable of augmenting spellcasting and multiple debilitating attacks in melee. "Would you like to use this weapon in your quest, or would you prefer the Crescent Blade of Eilistraee?" When subsequently throwing the Crescent Blade to Seyll Auzkovyn: "This blade was forged by Eilistraee as a weapon against her mother, Lolth. It's pale moon-fires pass through armor, and it can cleave even the head of a goddess from her shoulders." ===Post-quest=== When talking to Seyll Auzkovyn after the quest: "Welcome back, . How have you fared on your quest for the Amulet of Yendor?" When talking to Seyll Auzkovyn after getting the [[Amulet of Yendor|Amulet]]: "You have it! You have recovered the Amulet of Yendor! Now, I will tell you what must be done: "The Amulet has within it magic, the capability to transport you to the Astral Plane, where the high altar of Eilistraee resides. "To activate this magic, you must travel upwards as far as you can. When you reach the temple, sacrifice the Amulet to Eilistraee. "Thus will you fulfill your destiny." {{stub}} [[Category:dNethack]] [[Category:dNethack Quests]]
